<dl id="n18078c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n18" href="#n18078c">N18 (VI.B.8)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n18all.htm#n18078c"> 78(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Chinese put buddhas / into molluscs to be / pearled</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Centuries ago the Chinese were in the habit of deliberately introducing foreign bodies into the shells of fresh-water mussels, the pieces of grit, or even little metal images of Buddha, being eventually transformed with a coating of mother-of pearl. <small> E.G. Boulenger, <a name="EGBQ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGBQ"><cite title="source">Queer Fish and other inhabitants of the rivers and oceans</cite></a> (Aug 1925) 174</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
